## Installation Steps

### 1. Create Bootable USB

1. Download Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS ISO
2. Flash it to a USB drive using Balena Etcher
3. The flash drive may appear as two drives in Windows — this is normal

### 2. Prepare the Vivobook

1. Plug in the USB drive
2. Power on and press `F2` to enter BIOS
3. Set USB as first boot priority
4. Save and exit — Ubuntu installer will launch

### 3. Ubuntu Installation

1. Select language and keyboard layout
2. Configure network (or skip — can be done post-install)
3. Select "Erase disk and install Ubuntu" for a clean install
4. Complete installation and reboot

### 4. Install Dependencies

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install apache2 mysql-server -y
```

### 5. Install PHP 8.2

Ubuntu 22.04 ships with PHP 8.1, but Nextcloud requires 8.2. Add the Ondrej PPA:

```bash
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php
sudo apt update
sudo apt install php8.2 php8.2-mysql php8.2-xml php8.2-curl php8.2-gd \
  php8.2-mbstring php8.2-zip php8.2-intl php8.2-bcmath php8.2-imagick -y
```

Switch Apache to PHP 8.2:

```bash
sudo a2dismod php8.1
sudo a2enmod php8.2
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

### 6. Set Up the Database

```bash
sudo mysql -u root
```

Inside MySQL:

```sql
CREATE DATABASE nextcloud;
CREATE USER 'nextclouduser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'your-strong-password';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON nextcloud.* TO 'nextclouduser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;
```

> **Security note:** Use a strong, unique password. Do not use `password123` or any simple placeholder in production.

### 7. Download and Install Nextcloud

```bash
cd /var/www/html
sudo wget https://download.nextcloud.com/server/releases/latest.tar.bz2
sudo tar -xjf latest.tar.bz2
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html/nextcloud
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/nextcloud
```

### 8. Configure Apache

Create a virtual host config:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/nextcloud.conf
```

Add:

```apache
<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName 192.168.1.100
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html/nextcloud

    <Directory /var/www/html/nextcloud>
        Options +FollowSymlinks
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>
</VirtualHost>
```

Enable the site and required modules:

```bash
sudo a2dissite 000-default.conf
sudo a2ensite nextcloud.conf
sudo a2enmod rewrite headers env dir mime
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

### 9. Make Services Persistent

```bash
sudo systemctl enable apache2
sudo systemctl enable mysql
```

### 10. Configure a Static IP (Netplan)

Make network settings survive reboots:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/netplan/00-installer-config.yaml
```

```yaml
network:
  version: 2
  ethernets:
    enx6c11f764de12:
      dhcp4: no
      addresses:
        - 192.168.1.100/24
      routes:
        - to: default
          via: 192.168.1.1
      nameservers:
        addresses:
          - 192.168.1.1
```

Set correct permissions and apply:

```bash
sudo chmod 600 /etc/netplan/00-installer-config.yaml
sudo netplan apply
```

### 11. Access Nextcloud

Open a browser on any device on the same network and go to:

```
http://192.168.1.100
```

Complete the web setup wizard using the database credentials from Step 6.

